inn1.comm: full toss on off from over the wicket, 146ks, slight awayswing, gently pushed past the bowler to mid-off
143.2ks full awayswinger outside off, the opener has a leaden-footed slash and gets beaten in the channel
Starc pulls his length back outside off, Charles jabs it off an open face towards point

Starc celebrates his 50th ODI, with a wicket in the first over! Full temper in the channel, 144.5ks, nibbles away a touch outside off. Charles has another reckless leaden-footed slash and nicks it to captain Smith at second slip. Chest-high catch. Easily done
greets Bravo with a teasing outswinger, the new man does not bite
back of a length and around off, 146ks, guided towards point with soft hands
nice and full, angled in on off, blocked back coming forward
encouraging carry, back of a length and ignored outside off
pitched further up and comes in, Fletcher gets a bigger stride forward and plays it back to Hazlewood
back of a length and leaves Fletcher outside off, he has a roundhouse swing at it, and watches the ball beat the outside edge. Beaten by swing and bounce
141.3ks, full, incoming ball, blocked back, pressing forward
good length and curls away outside off, left alone watchfully. Back-to-back maidens
full and angled in from round the wicket, tapped back defensively
bouncer, tennis ball bounce, ducked under. Sqaure-leg ump Brathwaite signals a no-ball. First runs for WI. Far too high
swerving down the leg side, wide
outswinging full toss just a shade outside off, sliced drive to third man, past the two-man slip cordon. Rolls off an outside edge
nice and straight, 147ks, defended to the covers on the front foot. It tailed in a bit
length and outside off, Fletcher drives on the up and finds the man at cover-point. Bailey with the floppy hat
zippy short ball, 147ks, holds its line outside off, skirts past the outside edge. The right hander was opened up, searching for the away movement. Starc throws a verbal volley at the batsman
back of a length and comes in, takes the hip as Fletcher fails to flick it away
good length and angling away outside off from over the stumps, no shot offered
similar ball, left alone outside off by Bravo
probing line, closer to the off stump, Bravo watches it through to Wade
same line, more bounce on this, would have skirted over the fourth stump. Ignored
streaky four! Steven Smith applauds from behind. Back of a length and Hazlewood finds a hint of inward movement. Bravo aims to drive and sends an inside edge that rolls to the right of Wade
length ball, no swing, on the stumps, Bravo shows the full face of the bat and  unfurls a crackin' drive.... straight to mid-off
good length ball on off, blocked on the front foot
shortish away-going ball outside off, Fletcher jabs at it, only to watch the ball zip past the outside edge. There's the stare from Starc
back of a length and angled in, Fletcher gets off the mark on his 13th ball with a waft towards midwicket
veering into the pads, glanced behind square on the leg side
terrific inswinging yorker at the base of the off stump, the right hander jabs his bat down and digs it out. Steven Smith was excited behind the wicket
nasty, prancing delivery, pings the glove! 147.9ks. Starc fires another verbal volley. Intent from Starc. I like this Starc
short on off, Bravo drops it in front of his feet
good length on off, Bravo presses forward and defends to the covers
laced away to the right of mid-off. First bad ball of the day: Hazlewood serves up a half-volley outside off, driven with great authority. WI need more of this
angling away wide outside off, the left hander covers his off stump and leaves it be
short on off, 135ks, rushes onto Bravo, fended into the pitch
this full ball ducks into Bravo, wafted to slip off an edge
edged and Boland lumbers in from third man. It drops short of him and Boland concedes two. Good length and angled away, Fletcher aims for a big swipe over midwicket and skews it away
back of a length on off, defended to point. Another stare from Starc
full ball around off, Fletcher throws his hands and slices another outside edge, this clears Bailey at cover point
full incoming ball, tapped towards mid-off, Bravo wants a quick single. Fletcher was slow to take off. No direct hit and he makes it
soft full ball down leg, deflected off the thigh pad fine on the leg side, past a diving Wade
another loosener. Shortish and ample width outside off, 143ks. Fletcher isn't bother by it. He slashes it hard through backward point. Races away.... for Fletcher's first boundary
Hazlewood errs in length now, overpitched outside off, flows forward and wristily driven past the bowler for four

Bravo now nicks off. What an emphatic riposte. What a catch from Steven Smith at wide-ish slip. The extra bounce undid Bravo. The line is around off. Back of a length kicks up, angling away, finds the edge. Slip dives full-stretch to his right and comes out with the ball in his right hand
Hazlewood welcomes Samuels with a good bouncer, he sways his upper body out of the way
back of a length and rears up at off, Samuels is surprised and ends up gloving a single towards third man
Fletcher shuffles across, gets inside the line of this length ball and helps it to fine leg
bounce again! Wry smile from the bowler. Lifting ball outside off, not even close to full for the drive. Poor shot selection. Beaten

Starc takes down Fletcher, wins the battle, and roars! Short and angling away outside off, prancing delivery. Gets big on Fletcher and opens him up. The opener has a feeble waft and spoons a catch to Marsh at gully. WI three down
another lifting delivery outside off, 143.2ks, left alone
incoming ball, pokey drive to mid-on off an inside edge
good length and angled away, Starc snatches the outside edge, runs towards gully
overpitched and outside off, forward and driven straight to mid-off
Ramdin gets off the mark with a boundary.  Full and wide outside off, driven fluently through the covers
full and angled in, Samuels stabs a drive to short extra cover for one
back of a length and angled in, blocked towards mid-off
back of a length, guided towards point via an open face
back of a length and outside off, hangs back and jabs to the covers
leaping bouncer on the middle stump, extra pace and bounce, Ramdin rocks his head out of the way
good length and angled in, Ramdin inches forward and pushes it to cover point
floats a length ball across the batsman, who dabs it behind the wicket
width on offer and he's crunched that off the backfoot into the point boundary. Delightful timing, got on top of the bounce and boom!
much fuller and across Samuels, who watches it through to the keeper. That was the leg-cutter as well
beautiful delivery again, gets it to land just around the region where Samuels isn't sure whether to play forward or go back, left alone in the end
forces that off the backfoot to cover point
another slower delivery outside off, Samuels leaves and Wade has a tough task taking it on the second bounce. Slowness of the surface coming through already
good length ball on off stump, solidly defended
slower one on off stump, Ramdin inside-edges a drive to Boland at mid-on
invites Ramdin to blast one through cover, there's a hint of movement away from off stump, left alone
fantastic delivery again, draws him forward by floating it full on off stump, enough movement to create a doubt in the batsman's mind, watched through to the keeper
gets behind the line of the ball to bunt that to the off side
getting too predictable, and that's his USP, isn't it? Another full ball on off stump that's left alone by Ramdin
length ball on middle, Samuels gets back to punch that to cover

the heaven or hell approach from Samuels, no half-measures as he looks to clobber that over cover, but ends up getting a thick inside edge that races past Hazlewood at midwicket. Has enough legs to race into the boundary
lazy elegance to the fore, gets half-forward to ease that to cover
enough width for him to make some room and crunch that off the frontfoot to sweeper cover
looks to get across but ends up staying put on middle stump as he plays it back down the pitch
top shot! Shows the full face of the bat to ease that half-volley past mid-on. Short boundary there, and on this billiards top, there was no chance for the fielder to dish in a dive. Exquisite timing
full ball on off stump, steered to gully
angles a length ball into middle and leg, tucked to midwicket
shapes to pull but was through with the stroke when the ball rolled off the toe-end to mid-on. Clearly early into the stroke there, but it was there to be hit
uppish, but safe. Looks to hit it down the ground over the bowler's head, but the ball stops on him a touch to lob off the top half of the bat. Lands short of mid-on
crunching sound of the ball hitting the centre, but Bailey is upto the task at point as he stops what would have been a certain boundary otherwise
slow and full on middle, dabbed to the off side
fuller in length, on middle, played back with a straight bat

nudged off the pad to fine leg. Hazlewood fires a throw to the keeper, who inturn has a shy at the stumps at the bowler's end even as Ramdin desperately tries to hustle back after being refused the second by Marlon
tucks the length ball on middle and leg to fine leg
defended with soft hands to midwicket, wicket-to-wicket stuff from Faulkner
punched to short cover, Bailey the man there. Once again the ball stops on him a touch as he looks to force that through the gap
cuts, but straight to Maxwell at point
starts with a short one that holds onto the surface to prevent Samuels from going for a full-blooded cut shot, the ball rolls to mid-off as the bat face turns in his hand
play and a miss. This one holds its line after pitching at length on off stump, Samuels is squared up as the ball misses the bails by a whisker
floats one back in from wide of the crease, Samuels is hit high on the pad as he misses the across-the-line whip

appeal for caught behind, but umpire  Gregory Brathwaite   is unmoved. Samuels' feet are glued to the crease as he attempts to punch off the backfoot. Has a go at it but looks like it missed everything. Matthew Wade's reaction was a giveaway of sorts. He wasn't convinced there was an edge there. Smith went for the review straightaway, but as it turns out,  there isn't much to overturn the initial decision of 'not out'
the attempted run down to third man is intercepted by the point fielder
whipped off his hip past square leg, aggressive calling made the second possible
full-length delivery angling across, Samuels opens the bat face to ease it to the slip fielder
on the pads, worked with the angle to long-on
stays inside the crease and punches that back to the bowler
length ball slanted across the batsman, pushed to cover, tight bowling this
width on offer, crunched to sweeper cover
gets across and works it wide of midwicket for an easy single
how does he do this like a machine? Lands it a touch ahead of good length on off stump, defended back down the pitch
gets forward and defends again
banged in short, but slides it down leg, Samuels ducks under it
half-volley on the pads, flicked to deep midwicket
hustles Ramdin for pace as he goes back into the crease to work that wide of midwicket
back of length delivery on middle from wide of the crease, he hops back to angle it to point
starts off with a short ball outside off, pushed to cover
width on offer, cuts it to deep point to bring up >b> 2000 ODI runs
top shot, some punch in that stroke as he uses the bottom hand to essay that short ball to deep point
beaten by one that nips away late. Ramdin pokes at that one with minimal feet movement, was helped by the late movement
gets one to swing back in from off stump, defended back with a straight bat
stays inside the crease to dab the length ball to cover
turns it to the vacant midwicket region for an easy single
flicked off the pads past mid-on, where Mitch Marsh dishes in the slide to keep it down to a single
wonder if they're trying to trap him down leg. This one's floated into the pads, all Samuels needed to do was get a faint tickle to get a boundary, misses
opens the bat face to play that one to point
that's a fabulous shot! Picks the length early, moves leg side to open up the off side and then hammers that into the point boundary. There was a touch of arrogance there
nearly chopped it back onto the stumps. Feet glued to the crease as he looks to ease it to the off side, the ball bounces off the inside edge over the stumps
once again he gets on top of the bounce to crunch that to deep point
fractionally short on off, Samuels swivels on the back foot and flat-bats a pull towards midwicket. Starc dishes out a drive and creates an indentation on the ground
Marsh throws his head back in despair. Back of a length and kicks up outside off. Samuels throws his hands at a cut and is defeated by the lift
much fuller on off, Samuels guides it behind square on the off side for one
back of a length and outside off, punched out to point
length ball on off, pushed to mid-off on the front foot
back of a length on off, the late away movement defeats Ramdin. He hung his bat out and got beaten past the outside edge. Marsh throws his head back, again. Probing bowling
Samuels clears his front leg and launches it straight over the bowler's head. Bang! Length ball on middle, Samuels sends it clattering straight down the ground
West Indies find some momentum! Fuller on off, Samuels slices a drive through the covers, beats mid-off as well. Faulkner chases and slides in vain, by the edge of the boundary
back of a length and outside off, slapped away to deep point
shorter and outside off, Ramdin gets on top of the bounce and punches it to short extra cover
dug in short and outside off, Ramdin fetches it from there and pulls towards square leg, where the fielder dives over the ball and leaks runs
back of a length, targetting the top of off, punchily blocked back to the bowler
rising short ball on off, Samuels rises with it and drops it in front of his toes
Marsh goes too full on off, Samuels responds with a drilled drive, hits through the line, past the bowler for four
this is even better! Short and width outside off, Samuels leans back and cuts it firmly past Maxi at backward point for another boundary
Marsh pulls his length back and cramps Samuels for room, flat-batted towards mid-on
this is a peach, although Samuels was helped by the errant length. Overpitched and outside off, his feet do not move. But the hands give him the power. Driven through the covers
Samuels brings up his second successive half-century against Australia, with a poked four. Looks like a cutter on the leg stump, he aims a flick and sends a leading edge to third man
full and straight, Ramdin picks it away to the right of mid-on. Flicked for three
fraction short and wide outside off, Samuels gets his front leg out of the way and smears a cut to deep point
back of a length and outside off, jabbed to point
back of a length on off, forward and punched straight to mid-off
length and angled in, worked to midwicket
back of a length and angled in, tucked through backward square leg for one
Marsh tests Samuels with a bouncer outside off, he sways out of the way. Too high and wided
Samuels powers on. Dug in short on off, Marsh does not have much pace. 131ks, Samuels waits on the back foot for the pull. Hit over mid-on
short again on middle, cross seamer, Samuels stands outside leg and flaps a pull over Bailey at short midwicket
back of a length and outside off, Ramdin rises on top of the bounce and punches a single to the off-side sweeper
back of a length inducker, tucks up Samuels for room. Jammed out towards short midwicket
short and wide outside off, cut with a flamboyant flourish to sweeper cover
full and aimed at off, Ramdin camps back and clips a single wide of midwicket
skids on a back of a length and outside off, pushed to short extra cover
overpitched and outside off, driven to short extra cover
full on middle, no turn, blocked back to Finch
slider on middle, clipped to short midwicket
drifts in and turns a bit, pushed to short extra cover for a speedy single
full and straight, whipped through midwicket
Starc goes wide of the crease and skates this in from round the stumps. Ping! Hit on the pad
Finch signals six near the backward square leg boundary! Full and sliding into the pads, Ramdin picks it up with the wrists and dispatches it for a flat six
too full and veers in on off, whipped to deep midwicket
full and angled in, 147ks, Samuels pushes out with his hands and jabs to mid-off
yorker, homing in on middle, dug out
full and holds its line outside off, Samuels is left reaching for the ball. Sliced drive to third man ensues
flat and fired outside leg as Samuels backs away. Squeezed out
slider outside off, cuts and misses
full and turns away outside off, left alone
shorter and outside off, cut on the back foot through point
lobbed up full on middle, non-turning ball, driven inside-out to long-off
slid through on off, driven through the covers
short and angled in on middle, 145ks, defended back
short, veers in and cramps the batsman for room. Fended towards square leg. The two batsmen get together and punch gloves, first 100 partnership for WI this series
full incoming ball, Ramdin drives and squirts an inside edge behind square
full, full enough for the drive. Samuels plays uppishly to short extra cover

Wade dives to his right and shells it Starc nearly had the breakthrough with the cutter. Full and swerves away outside off from round the wicket, Samuels has a leaden-footed push and edges it. Wade drops it as the ball rolls between keeper and slip
149ks leaping ball, pings the glove and rolls to square
dabbed to the leg side
Samuels marches down the track, manufactures a full ball, and drives down the ground to reach 5000 ODI runs
Samuels steps out and gets a full toss, bunted to long-on
length ball on the off stump, Ramdin targets it and swipes it over vacant midwicket
short and spins away wide outside off, flat-batted away to wide long-off
cramps Samuels for room. Quicker one at 88ks, Chopped from off stump to point
dear me! Nearly. Looks to flick, and gets a leading edge that lobs over Smith's outstretched hands at cover
incoming delivery from wide of the crease, left alone
width and belted. Picks the gap between point and short third man. He took the pace off the ball, but it didn't matter. Faulkner knew it was a bad ball the moment he delivered it
stays inside the crease and dabs that to point
worked with the angle to long-on, easy single taken
gets a thick inside edge to square leg, Faulkner mutters a few words to the batsman.
turns it with the spin to midwicket
makes a bit of room and cuts to deep point
pushed through quicker on middle and leg, nudged to short fine leg
fires one down leg, Wade does well to get across to half-stop that
short, gets away with that as Samuels mistimes the cut to cover
worked with the spin to midwicket, Samuels will keep strike
dead bats an incoming delivery from wide of the crease
drops it into the off side for a quick single
defended off the backfoot to the off side
on the pads, worked into the square leg region
full ball on off stump, stabbed to the man coming in from point
worked with the spin to deep midwicket
too short, he makes a bit of room and cuts that into the gap at deep cover
bowls a slider down leg, good take by Wade
too short again, crunched to deep point this time
poor ball and is lucky to get away. Too short, Samuels cuts it straight to point
worked with the spin to short fine leg for a quick single
on the shorter side, whipped to midwicket
defended with a dead bat, the inside edge rolls off the pad to the off side
steered to Bailey at point, wants the single but quickly changes his mind
whipped to midwicket, Ramdin was backing up a long way but no damage done in the end
defends the incoming full delivery to short midwicket
length ball on middle and leg, turned wide of square leg
floats it full on middle and leg, eased down to long-on
tapped wide of point to bring up his  eighth ODI fifty.  He soaks in the applause of the dressing room, top knock
flat-batted pull to deep square leg
gets inside the line of the ball and helps the short ball down to fine leg
poor direction, too short and well outside the wide line, Samuels looks to play an upper cut but couldn't reach that one
looks for a single, and will get it. All he did was simply tap that gently to the off side to set off for the run. Ramdin was off the blocks spontaneously
uses the pace of the bowler to angle it wide of a diving Maxwell at point

just over short fine leg. Loaded with risk, but it was too poor a delivery, which he somehow took toll of. Length ball angling down leg, and he's simply used the pace to pick him over the fielder there
gets a thick edge while attempting a drive, lands short of short third ma
driven down the ground to long-off
dabbed to point, they complete the run in a jiffy
gets a thick inside edge past the bowler, to long-on
incoming length delivery, dropped wide of the bowler on the leg side for a quick single
length ball on off stump, tapped gently to point for a quick single
cut away, but will find the sweeper at deep point
gets on top of the bounce and bunts it to point
not much room to work with again, point comes into play again to stop that dab
uses the pace to run the incoming length ball down to third man

shapes to play a flat-batted pull, but it was an excellent short ball that was angling into middle from wide of the crease. Ramdin was hurried for pace as well and in the end he simply swayed out of the way
hops across to work it off his hi
picks the length early and uses his wrists to work it behind square on the leg side, fine leg had no chance there. Super placement, bisected the gap perfectly
pulled in front of square to deep midwicket
slower one on middle, turned to midwicket
full length delivery on off stump, there's an invitation to drive, but Samuels lets that go
accurate stuff, not much room, the full ball is bunted back to the bowler
toe-ends a mow to deep midwicket, where Khawaja does the mopping up
wonderful stroke. Genuine gift, and he takes full toll, Too short, he makes room and slaps that in front of square, one bounce into the cover boundary.
picks the bones out of that pull, but can't pick the gap, Khawaja in action again at deep midwicket
swung across the line, gets a thick inside edge down to deep fine leg, looks like he's decided enough is enough
excellent bouncer, Samuels was waiting for it yes, but couldn't have played the pull with the ball being delivered at close to 140 clicks
once again the pace of the ball means the ball rushes onto him as he shapes to play the pull, which lobs to mid-off
angles a yorker-length delivery back in from round the stumps, Samuels is beaten on the drive as the ball rolls to the keeper
leans forward and eases the drive to deep cover, 200 up for West Indies. Applause around the ground
he's clobbered that! Clears his front leg and slaps that over long-on. Disdainfully done. This was too full, he made a bit of room and swung through the line to make clean connection

and another one! This is even better. Some savage hitting this. Starc angles it full, it was right in the slot for Ramdin, who simply lofted through the line. The ball nearly hit those expensive ultra-motion camera near the sightscreen
uses the pace of the bowler to run it down to third man this time
driven down to long-off
loopy cutter outside off, run down to third man
Hazlewood rolls his fingers across this full one outside off and beats the drive
full and arrowed through on middle, Ramdin walks across off and clips it to fine leg. They hare across for the second. Well done!
too straight again, glanced to fine leg again
tennis ball bounce on this short ball on off, Samuels guides a pull towards fine leg
near yorker on middle, whipped to midwicket
wild full ball down the leg side from round the stumps, wide
yorker, skates in on off, dug out towards point for one
Starc sends down a crackin ball, a lifter, something that defined his first spell. 147ks, this. Samuels hops and skips. Loosens his grip and fends it towards point
low full toss on off, guided towards deep point

Back of a length and veers in, Ramdin aims for a roundhouse swipe across the line and does not connect. Timbaah! Ramdin acknowledges a cheers as he walks back. Starc finally finds a way past this pair. The quick hit the top of middle
banged in short and angled in, pings the glove and runs towards square leg
yorker just outside off, 146ks, can't be squeezed out
dug in short and gets big on KP, he cushions it into the pitch
lifting ball outside off, Pollard was late to hook, sends a top edge over Wade
follows it with another nasty bouncer, this is directed just outside off. KP fends it towards third man
yorker, homing in, squirted behind square off an inside edge
short and homing in on the ribs, worked gently to square leg for one
full and straight, bunted down the ground
full and angled in on middle from round the stumps, tucked to the midwicket region. A direct hit from Bailey could have dismissed Pollard at the keeper's end. Sloppy running from the big man
full toss on middle, pushed to mid-off
Starc hammers a short ball and cramps Pollard for room. Pollard was taking evasive action. Off the forearm to the keeper. The batsmen cross over. And it has been called a dead ball
yorker outside off, can't be jammed out. Beaten.
short and angled in, helped to long leg
too full and outside off, eased to short extra cover for one
back of a length and attacking the body, guided to fine leg
Pollard nearly swung himself off his feet! Full and outside off, having backed away, Pollard flays and misses
short ball on off, flapped away to fine leg

there it is! There is Samue's moment. He has played 16 years against Australia, and this is his first century against them. The crowd bursts into cheers. This has been some knock. He kisses the helmet and gets a hug from KP. Full and straight, he goes deep in the crease and clips it towards square leg

caught at the edge of the boundary Maxwell signals a six. Back of a length and angled in, Pollard clouts it in the air. Shovelled it, in fact. Maxwell pouched it, but lost momentum as his left foot touched the rope at the deep midwicket boundary
back of a length on middle, clipped to the leg side
113ks slower bouncer, foxes KP
slower short ball outside off, Pollard swings early and misses

The short ball pins down Pollard. Leaping ball outside off, quicker one from Boland. Pollard, looking to pull, drags it from outside off. Marsh runs to his right and takes it comfortably at deep midwicket
yorker outside off, driven through the covers
bouncer outside off, left alone, too high. Wide
too full and outside off, flayed to long-off
full and outside off, run down to short third man
back of the hand legcutter outside off, the batsman waits on it and forces it past backward point for four
yorker at the toes, jabbed down to long-on
short and angled in, open-faced dab to backward point. Third man is up as well
length ball on off, Carlos clears his front leg for a swipe. Ends up slicing over extra cover
back of the hand legcutter, Samuels cuts it away for four again. Placed it between backward point and third man
legcutter too full, jammed out to the covers
yorker on off, backs away and squeezes to the covers
dug in short and outside off, Carlos winds up and swats to wide long-on
Boland aims for the yorker, goes too full on off, Carlos clears his front leg and smears it to the right of mid-off. Smacked to the boundary
great reply from Boland. Pinpoint yorker on off, dips under the bat and tilts the middle stump back. Some more reward for Boland at the death
slower bouncer on off, 116.4ks, fended to the leg side for one
Boland misses the yorker and serves it up too full on middle, Samuels jumps outside leg and blasts a straight down. Bombs away!
Holder holes out! Looks like the back of the hand legcutter. Full and outside off. Holder attacks it and ends up slicing it straight into the lap of sweeper cover
short on middle, heaved to Finch at long-on
back of the hand slower one outside off, Narine swings early and does not touch it
back of a length and outside off, whipped to long-on

Samuels clears Maxwell and gets six! He stepped outside leg and was chased by a back of a length ball. Clouted over midwicket. Maxi aimed to leap in the air, take it, and flick the ball back into play by the edge of the boundary. No dice. No balance. Six
No, he is dismissed off the last ball of WI's innings. What a reception for him! Full and outside off, Samuels swings and ends up slicing a catch to sweeper cover

inn2.comm: Brathwaite dives to his right at mid-off to keep that full-blooded off drive to a single
crashed into the cover boundary. Overpitched and he put that away easily. Foot forward before he powered that between cover and mid-off
slides one into middle and leg, the ball deflects of the thigh pad as he looks to work it past square leg
too straight again, clipped away off the pads to deep fine leg, easy pickings those
hits the deck hard, angles a length ball across Khawaja, who bunts it to mid-off for a quick single
whipped off his hip towards deep backward square leg. Runs of every delivery in this over
picked away off his pads. Poor start, too full and he eases that towards deep square leg
much better. Not much room to work that length ball angling away, tapped back down the pitch
too short on leg stump, worked off his hip to deep square

this one's a juicy half-volley on the pads, Khawaja will put those away even in his sleep. Balance, timing and placement perfect as he picks that one away into the midwicket boundary. Excellent wrist work
hops back to turn the short ball on middle to midwicket
flicked, but straight to mid-on this time
plays the upper cut with ease. Sitting up nicely for him to free his arms and throw the kitchen sink at that, Finch does just that. One bounce into the ropes at deep point
pulled in front of square, imperious! Picks the length early and fetches the pull from outside off. Struck that cleanly, nearly went all the way!
nips back in from outside off, he pushes outside the line to get a thick inside edge to square leg
looks to flick, gets a leading edge that rolls to mid-off as they complete the run. Closed the bat face early there
driven on the up, straight to mid-off. Better length that, Finch was briefly in two minds
beaten by a jaffa! Finch is squared up as he shapes to defend the length ball that nips away ever-so-late. Top stuff
lands a half-volley on the pads, flicked to mid-on again
clipped towards Carter at deep midwicket, at the moment, he's operating on just one side of the wicket here
feeds him with a half-volley on the pads again, this time Khawaja works it much square to the boundary rider
slides into middle and leg, looks to nudge it leg side, the ball deflects off the pad to short fine as they scamper through for a run
ball hurries onto the bat as Khawaja mistimes an attempted off drive to mid-off
much better, floats it at length on middle, Khawaja is a touch squared up as he pats it back to the bowler
immediately gets some lift off the deck as Finch hops back to run that down to third man
angling into the pads, clipped to deep square leg

uppish and there's the first wicket. Finch is clearly hustled for pace as he hops back to whip it to square leg. He had to fetch the ball from outside off as the extra bounce means the ball lobs off the leading edge to mid-on. Brathwaite is pumped as he leaps in joy to celebrate that. So the bowling change has worked for the hosts!
solidly behind the line as he bunts it back to the bowler
gets across the stumps to pat that incoming length ball back to the bowler
slower and fuller on off stump, squeezed to point. Excellent first over

first ODI wicket for Gabriel, and it's a peach to get Khawaja. Angles a length ball across after all those deliveries on the pads, and is rewarded immediately. This was bowled at an angle where Khawaja simply had to play, and he made the mistake of playing with an angled bat as the thin edge is well pouched by Ramdin, diving to his right. Joy for West Indies. They're delighted as Gabriel is mobbed by his team-mates. Two in two!
keeps out that full delivery on middle using a straight bat
straightens off length on middle, Bailey hops back and defends
bread and butter stroke. Can't ask for a better delivery first up, can you? On the pads, and he works it wide of mid-on. Pressure released with that buffet ball
pushed off the backfoot to cover point
the edge flies into the third man boundary. Lucky, but it doesn't matter for Australia. Looks to slash, went hard at it and got the result he desired in the end
punched to cover point, top work by Charles but couldn't prevent the run. He moved swiftly to his left
gets back and across as he punches the length ball on off stump to cover
punched again, straight to cover
squared up as the edge flies to third man
pulled, but can't pick the gap. He fetched it from outside off alright, but hit it straight to midwicket
shows the full face of the bat to tap it back down the pitch

beaten by a peach! That one was bowled at 148.5 clicks. Bailey was clearly late to get down on that length ball that deviated just a touch after pitching on off stump. That wasn't far away from the nick
lets that go. The ball nips back in sharply from outside off
the ball thuds into the pad as Bailey is half-forward while defending
in the slot to drive, hit straight to mid-off
not quite there for the cut, he went through despite being cramped for room, chopped to cover point
angles it full on middle from wide of the crease, pushed to cover.  Maiden over
opens the bat face late to bunt the length ball to point, refuses the single immediately
kept low and he nearly dragged it back onto the stumps. The ball rolls to the keeper off the bottom of the bat
misfield at cover gives away two runs. It was a firm push, and Benn made a mess of that by dishing in an awkward dive. He slipped as he went down
imperious pull! Picks the length early, rolls his wrists to keep the ball down and picks the gap at square leg. Easy pickings

crunching cover drive. The followthrough of the bat as he made the connection was copy book style. In the slot and he climbed onto that in a jiffy. Got a touch across to make the contact. Stillness as he made contact was the key. Outstanding
gets half-forward as he defends to cover
that's the shot of the evening. Too short, and Bailey forces that off the backfoot into the point boundary. Got on top of the bounce to play that
drives, but takes the bottom hand off the grip as he makes contact. Ball stopped on him
hops back to defend a full-length delivery to Pollard at point
once again on the shorter side, forced to Fletcher at extra cover
shuffles across to defend a length ball back down the pitch
gets a thick inside edge onto the pad as he looks to drive through cover
and Bailey welcomes us with a cut four. Dropped short and outside off, Bailey skips back and slaps it past covers
short and outside off, cracks a cut through backward point
short again, this one turns past the outside edge
darts another short ball and gives width, Bailey rocks back and cracks another cut through backward point. No chance for Carlos, chasing from sweeper cover, and then sliding
Benn held this back and finds sharp turn outside off, glided to short third man
lobbed up full on off, Bailey bends forward in defence
full and skids on middle, flicked to backward square leg
flighted full on off, tapped to long-on
pushed through shorter on off, punched down to long-on
full and straight, Smith whips it sweetly through midwicket
tucked off the thigh pad to backward square leg
another one tucked off the hips to backward square leg. This time they chance a single, and get an extra run via an overthrow
drifts in on the leg stump, Smith hangs back, searching for a flick and gets a leading edge towards the covers
dragged down short on middle, Smith skips back and nails a pull to the midwicket boundary
shorter and turns outside off, square-cut away
arm-ball, snakes in on off, blocked back to the bowler
flighted, grips and turns outside off, prodded towards the covers
Bailey uses his feet, does not quite get close to the pitch, and plays a checked drive to mid-off
straighter one from Narine, patted down to long-on
shorter knuckle ball, cut to deep point
Smith presses forward to smother any spin
floated on off, forward and defended to the leg side
offbreak, Smith glances to backward square leg
full and at off, driven smoothly to long-on for one more
flat and turns away outside off, pushed to point
Benn is not getting his lengths right, shorter and outside off, square-cut away, again
better... fuller on off, defended
slider on off stump, chopped to the covers, risky picking from the stumps
Bailey takes a trip down the pitch and milks this full one down to long-on
quicker one, 96ks, on off, defended back to Benn
dropped short and outside off, camps back and punches a single to long-on
slower through the air on off, just 79ks, played back
breaking down leg, wide
Smith hangs back and punches this flat one from the middle-stump line to long-on
whipped to the right of KP at short midwicket
pushed very full on off, driven to long-on
tossed on off, Bailey gets forward and across to smother it
drifts in full on off, poked out to cover
and Benn goes flat and quick outside off, Smith dabs a cut, stepping back after having ventured forward. Played late past Holder at lone slip
Benn opens Smith up! Drifts in and rips away past the outside edge. Top ball
very full on off, driven to long-off
flattish on off, whipped down to long-on
dropped short and outside off, steps back and cuts to square point - Bravo
drifting down leg, paddled straight to short fine leg
flighted full on off, Bailey gets a big stride forward and defends
quicker offbreak, on the back foot, punching to short midwicket
full and straight, dabbed defensively to short midwicket
full offbreak on middle, nudged to short midwicket
whipped off the hips past square leg
tossed on middle, driven to long-off
full on middle, shuffles across and whips down to long-on

soft, soft dismissal! Bailey falls, three balls after the drinks break. Length ball, drifts in on off, grips in the surface, and turns away. Bailey is left searching for a leg-side flick. Instead, he plops a leading edge into the lap of KP at short extra cover
fullish on off, defended to short extra cover on the front foot
pushed quicker on off, blocked off the front foot again
blockhole ball at off, jammed back to Benn
might have been a knuckle ball outside off, passes the outside edge
shortish on off, punched to long-on
too short outside off, forced to long-on
pretty full and beats the flick. Hits the pad but this floater was heading down loeg
leg-stump ball, picked away to square leg
legbreak from Narine, stops on the batsman. Marsh pops it wide of short extra cover
grip and turn from middle, Smith half-pushes it to the off side
played with the spin to cover, again a hint of turn from middle
shapes to cut but this one bounces a bit more than he expected, rolls to cover
drifts into middle, Marsh lunges forward to smother the spin
quicker one on off stump, this one holds its line, Marsh is cramped for room as he undercuts it
drawn forward by the flight, squeezed to point. Top over
slower one on middle, worked off his hip to midwicket
slides one down leg, good take by Ramdin who moves swiftly to his left
gift, and put away. Onto the pads and he's tickled that into the fine leg boundary. To bowl there is a sin
bunted wide of point for an easy single
shuffles across and pulls towards deep backward square leg, the fielder was caught napping and Smith was off the blocks quickly for the second
worked to deep square leg for an easy single
slower one on off stump, bunted towards point for an easy single. Sensible stuff
driven with the spin to deep cover
drifting into middle, squeezed to short third man as he looks to drive
driven with the spin to cover, played that with a degree of caution
quicker one on off, touch fuller as well, eased to sweeper cover
cuts away sharply from outside off, he crunches a cut to deep cover
steps out but Benn slows it down nicely, Smith can only lunge forward to smother the spin
turned to midwicket
firm push down the ground to long-off
floats it full on off, Smith's attempted backfoot force rolls to point as they scamper through for a quick single
full on the pads, worked to long-on
lands it on middle from wide of the crease, driven to long-on
too full on the pads, he flicks it from off stump to long-on
squeezed to third man, didn't have much room to work with
shuffles across to work it past midwicket, but makes the late adjustment and defends
sweetly timed, but the drive finds Benn at cover
pulled well, but straight to deep midwicket. Fletcher fires a direct hit at the bowler's end, but the batsmen had no intention of taking the second anyway
imperious! Key to playing the pull with that angle was to pick the length early, which he did. Rolled his wrists over the ball to keep it down. Raced away into the deep square leg boundary
flicked into the gap between deep midwicket and long-on, runs starting to flow here
excellent stop off his own bowling, moves to his right on the followthrough to intercept that drive
forced off the backfoot to long-on
dabs it to point for an easy single
not much room this time, floated full on middle from wide of the crease, tapped to midwicket
full and straight on middle and leg, clipped to deep midwicket
welcome boundary! Have to say it was a poor ball. A half-volley on the pads, and he's worked that into the gap at deep midwicket
floats a length ball on off stump, pushed to point
shuffles across to whip, but the extra bounce means the ball thuds into the thigh pad, they steal a leg-bye
solidly behind the line of that incoming length ball
straightens off a length on middle, rolls back down the pitch off a leading edge
back of length delivery on off stump, bunted to cover

another over where the last delivery has been picked for a boundary. Not a convincing drive, but runs nonetheless. Shapes to go over cover, but ends up slicing it behind point. Third man was too fine and had no chance
quicker one on middle and leg, ball deflects off the pad to short fine
worked with the spin to long on
fires a quicker one on the stumps, Marsh is deep inside the crease as he defends
whipped across the line to deep square leg
too full, doesn't get underneath it, squeezed to midwicket
breaks back into middle, Smith makes a bit of room and plays it late and behind square to the boundary rider at point
induces the edge, but there's no one to pouch it. Marsh shapes to drive, only to be beaten by a delivery that holds its line, and the ball races off the thick edge into the third man boundary
misfield at cover gives them a run that wasn't on. Sloppy from Samuels, who was on the move as the ball was punched to him
pushed to point, hint of hesitation but he hares across to get to the non-striker's end,  a direct hit from Darren Bravo and Smith would have been walking back
floats one full on middle from wide of the crease, bunted back to the bowler
solid thump in that drive on the up, straight to cover
inside-edges a drive to long-on
worked with the spin to deep square leg
sharp turn back in, there's square leg in place to stop that whip
on the shorter side, crunched to deep point. Smith is disappointed that he couldn't take full toll of that, lets out a cry of anguish
this one turns away, gently dabbed to cover for a quick single
pushed through quicker, but loses direction. Excellent take down leg
gets across the stumps and works it to midwicket
this one's the carrom ball, Smith is solidly behind the line as he bunts it to cover
fraction short on off, Marsh camps back and pulls over midwicket
back of a length and angled in, Smith walks forward and glides a single towards point
short and outside off, Marsh swings hard, so hard that his bottom hand flies off the bat handle. Slashed to point. Smith is eager for the single and gets it
back of a length on off, shuffles across and clips behind square
offcutter on middle, waited and helped to fine leg
low full toss on off, squirted behind square on the off side and Steven Smith acknowledges his half-century, three on the trot this tri-series
legbreak outside off, steered to point
lobbed up on middle, dips, poked back. Offbreak?
dragged short and outside off, Smith muscles a pull to wide long-on
short legbreak, half-tracker, pulled to deep midwicket from outside off
straighter one, pushed back to Fletcher
Smith shovels this short ball from outside off to long-on
back of a length and zings in from outside off, beaten past the inside edge
Smith walks across off to meet this back of a length ball on off. Whipped to deep midwicket
short and just outside off, not enough room to work with, slashed to point
yorker outside off, 149ks, the batsman is beaten for pace. Late to bring his bat down jab it
low full toss on off, pushed to mid-off
back of a length on off, pushed to mid-off again
floated on middle, nice and full, defended back
legbreak on off, run away to point
Smith steps out and manufactures a full toss. Whipped out to backward square leg
drops the legbreak short and outside off, clunked to deep cover
down the track and clipped to wide long-on, Smith aims for the second, they eventually decide against it
short and spins away outside off, cut through the covers
short and outside off, cut away to point
back of a length and outside off, carved over the covers. It does not carry to Johnson Charles at sweeper
good length on off, blocked to short extra cover
back of a length and around off, glided to backward point. A direct hit from Bravo could have got Marsh. He would have been out by a mile
full and straight, flicked in the air, does not carry to KP at short midwicket
back of a length and outside off, helped to third man
full on middle, nudged through midwicket
drifting outside leg, clipped through square leg
full on off, driven to long-off
Smith skips out and meets a full toss, which is drilled  back at Fletcher. It drops short of him
slides on outside off, chopped to point
flat and full on middle, bunted to long-on
drifts in full on middle, defended to short extra cover
Marsh raises a fifty of his own. Tossed on off, driven through the covers
down the track and eased through the covers
tossed on middle, spins away a touch, Marsh miscues it over the covers
dab-and-run single towards point as this was nice and full on middle
slides on off, patted to the covers for one
full cutter down leg, offbreak goes wide
not too short, not too wide to cut. Smith flashes and misses the roller
another offcutter down leg, second wide of the over
shortish on off, tapped down to long-on
lifting offcutter on middle, fended to short midwicket
full on off, shuffles across and whips to short midwicket
back of a length and outside off, punchily driven to the left of short extra cover
full and outside off, this cutter is wristily picked up over midwicket
down the track and yorks himself. Jammed out to short extra cover
dragged from outside off towards short fine leg off the inside half
Benn fires a full toss at off, 101.3ks, squeezed back to the bowler
blockhole ball on off, pushed to long-off
shot! Smith advances and backs away outside leg to meet this full ball. He unfurls an inside-out drive over extra cover

The sub fielder Carter nails a direct hit from short midwicket at the non-striker's end, but the Australia captain is home. Slides his bat in and makes it. He clipped this one to the leg side and rushed off
length ball on off, driven to long-on
105ks back of a length offcutter, sticks in the surface, Marsh punches it back. Pollard dives to his right in his followthrough. It does not stick
back of a length and outside off, steered to point
back of a length and outside off, Marsh unleashes a cut, splitting backward point and short third man
slapped to point, diving save from Carter
floated full and outside off, eased through point
slower delivery on the stumps from wide of the crease, squeezed to short third man where Narine effects a tumbling stop
picks the length early and pulls in front of square, didn't entirely get hold of it, wide long-on runs around to cut that off
stifled lbw appeal as Marsh looks to work across the line, the ball deflects off the pad to third man. There was appreciable bounce there, and so the ball would have comfortably missed the stumps
on the pads, worked with the angle to deep midwicket
yorker-length delivery on middle,  squeezed down to long-on
strays down leg side, worked to deep midwicket
steps out to take it on the full and squeeze it past cover
smears the full toss between long-on and long-off, wasn't off the middle but he hit it hard into the ground to get it over the bowler's head
hammered, but straight back to the bowler

that's the wicket West Indies were longing for. Smith doesn't even wait to see what the third umpire has to offer. It was a full toss which Marsh whipped to wide long-on. A second didn't look on but they decided to chance their luck, and unfortunately it didn't work this time. Darren Bravo fired the throw at the bowler' end on the bounce, and Benn collected that cleanly before swiftly dislodging the bails to beat Smith's desperate full-length dive. Is that the breakthrough that turns it around for West Indies? The game is back in the balance
flicks the low full toss to long-on again
beaten by square turn. This one drifts in, and then rips away from the rough to beat Maxwell comprehensively
helped towards fine leg, wrong line there, he was sliding the length ball into the pads
into the blockhole, squeezed to deep backward square leg, Maxwell fell over slightly as he made contact
another attempted yorker, jams his bat down in time to direct that towards long-on
drives, gets a thick inside edge to midwicket. The ball tailed back in slightly to beat him in that stroke
another yorker-length delivery on middle, bunted to long-on
low full toss outside off, finds the cover fielder. Just four of the over, pressure building

this one cuts back in sharply to sneak through the big gap between Maxwell's bat and pad as he shapes to cut. He thought the ball would spin the other way. It beat the keeper too, as it trickled towards fine leg
quicker one on middle and leg, but it was sliding down leg, Ramdin collects cleanly. Wide called
plays a premeditated reverse sweep, but finds short third man. Not in control, you have to say
not there to cut, but he somehow manages to squeeze that full delivery past cover for a single
flatter one that breaks back into middle and leg, Marsh is struck on the pad as he looks to nurdle it past square leg
this one's a cleverly-disguised leg-cutter, which Marsh defends
flat-bats a pull to long-on, excellent over again from Narine
pulls and misses, Ramdin half-stops it but ensures the pace is taken off the ball, Ashley Nurse, filling in for Holder, stops that at short fine leg

backs away and smacks that over cover, one bounce into the boundary. This was too full, and he made sure he got underneath the length to pick the boundary. Mid-off was up, and that perhaps gave him the confidence to play that stroke
excellent comeback, yorker-length ball a 145 clicks, Maxwell was through with the swing even before the ball got to him
sees the batsman trying to make room and bowls it full and wide, Maxwell can't reach out. The ball was well inside the wide line.  Smart bowling

solid connection, one bounce into the long-off boundary. Those strong forearms to the fore! Gabriel looks for the blockhole but misses his length by an inch, if not more, and it's enough for the batsman to get underneath the length.
through the inner ring, squeezed between cover and point, they're back for the second
leg-cutter on off stump, worked across the line to long-on
walks across to sweep, but the ball fizzed off the surface to beat his swing and deflect off the thigh pad to short fine leg
he's clobbered that, but straight to deep midwicket

is that the six that changes his fortunes? Maxwell at his destructive best. This time he brings out the switch hit and slaps it over deep point. Off the middle of the bat.  That's the first boundary Narine has conceded today
worked behind square on the leg side for an easy single
short outside off, crunched to deep point
thick inside edge to long-on, wanted to go straight, but ends up dragging it
slower one on middle, nudged to short fine leg
eased between cover and point, sensible stuff
misfield by Samuels at cover, and it has cost them a boundary. Drills a yorker-length delivery, Samuels lets it though his legs. Elementary stuff. Got up a little too early

this time he brings out the cross-batted swipe over deep midwicket. This was too full and he picked the bones out of that one. Darren Bravo leaps high to stop that, but can only get his finger tips to that. At no stage was he in control

this time the back-blade hit from Maxwell, or is it? Too short and angling in, he changes the grip helps that past short third man. Is he back? I dare say yes. Surely this over has all but sealed it for Australia.
bunted down to long-on for an easy single
walks across the stumps and whips it into the gap at wide long-on, called for two immediately
fired into the pads, and Maxwell has swept that into the fine leg boundary. Quickly gets down on one knee and uses the pace to help it into the boundary
swipes that across the line, to deep midwicket
punched to deep point, sensible stuff from Mitch Marsh
gets to the pitch of the ball and nurdles it to backward square leg
chips one over midwicket for a single
driven through the line to Carter at mid-off,  scores level, another opportunity for Maxwell to get a fifty
looks to whip it away but ends up playing it back to the bowler
game, set and match - Australia . On the pads, and he's worked that towards deep midwicket to complete the win
